  "block-handbooktitle-ecable": "Usage",
  "block-handbooktext-ecable": "Allows transmitting electrical energy over a distance. Can only be placed on solid faces of blocks. Insulated cable variants reduce losses by half!<br>Read about the operating features in the <a href=\"handbook:\/\/gamemechanicinfo-electricalprogressive-princip\">guide<\/a>.",

  // ==================== Thermogenerator and Thermoplates ====================
  "termogen": "Thermogenerator",
  "block-etermogenerator-*": "Thermoelectric Generator",
  "block-handbooktitle-etermogenerator": "Usage",
  "block-handbooktext-etermogenerator": "Converts thermal energy into electrical energy! Runs on anything that supports combustion. The higher the combustion temperature of the fuel, the greater the output power. Output power also slightly depends on the ambient temperature: the lower the ambient air temperature, the greater the energy generation. It does not work by itself - it requires <a href=\"handbook:\/\/block-electricalprogressivebasics:termoplastini-south\">thermoelectric plates<\/a> installed at the back.<br><br>Can be loaded with fuel automatically using hoppers.",

  "termoplastini": "Thermoelectric Plates",
  "block-termoplastini-*": "Thermoelectric Plates",
  "block-handbooktitle-termoplastini": "Usage",
  "block-handbooktext-termoplastini": "Thermoelectric plates are used in thermoelectric generators to convert thermal energy into electrical energy. The operating principle is based on the generation of thermoelectromotive force at the contact point of two dissimilar metals. The temperature difference is created by smoke from combustible fuel on one side and ambient air on the other side.<br><br>Placed behind the <a href=\"handbook:\/\/block-electricalprogressivebasics:etermogenerator-south\">thermoelectric generator<\/a>, up to 10 pieces. Can only be attached to the copper pad of the heat exchanger. Each subsequent section provides a smaller power increase. In total, 10 thermoplates will give 100% power to the thermogenerator. Two generators can be used on the same set of thermoelectric plates.",

  // ==================== Solar Generator ====================
  "block-esolargenerator-*": "Solar Panel Generator",
  "block-handbooktitle-esolargenerator": "Usage",
  "block-handbooktext-esolargenerator": "Converts light into electrical energy! The more sunlight hits the solar panel, the more energy it can produce. Blocks placed above the solar panel will reduce its efficiency. In late autumn and winter, sunlight decreases, leading to reduced efficiency.",

